titleStmt.title: Fóstbræðra saga according to AM 132 fol : A digital edition

publicationStmt.date: Converted from database and adapted to Menota, 15 February 2020

msIdentifier.msName: Fóstbræðra saga according to AM 132 fol (Möðruvallabók)

msContents.p: OEH: Description of the contents of the manuscript may be added here

origin.p: This manuscript was written in Iceland c. 1330-1370.

projectDesc.p: This encoding follows the standard set out in The Menota handbook (version 3.0), at http://www.menota.org/handbook.xml.
The encoded text has numbered pagebreaks, columnbreaks and linebreaks according to the manuscript.

normalization.p: This manuscript text has been encoded on three levels: facsimile, diplomatic and normalised.

correction.p: OEH: Comments on the correction may be added here.

interpretation.p: Words missing in the manuscript text and added by the editor are lemmatized and morphologically analyzed, except when occurring in a verse.
Headings were not included in the original database, but have been added in this version in all 3 versions and have been lemmatized and analyzed.
Verses have been added to the database in all 3 versions. Lemmatization and morphological analysis is provisional and will probably need correcting by an expert in skaldic verse.
